question: In tsiat-tang tsi̍t-ê tùi-chhiú, Kansas State tìng-thâu ê su-iâⁿ phēng,Karen kah tsòe-kīn 5-pái súi bē?
Tī chitê piáu lāi-bīn, Kansas State t total chiâⁿ-ê bâⁿ chha̍h só͘-ū tùi-chhiú lóng phah kúi ki?
Hñ oei si oih kuah KSU tiuh chēⁿ kó͘ ê tùi-chhiú?
Si jī-pōaⁿ ê tùi-chhiú sī siáⁿ-chiáⁿ ê, in ê chòe-chìn-chi̍t-pái pí-sài sī tī 1990 nî chiân kiat-sùk ê?
Chhoán-chāi ūi hō͘ KSU ūi tiāⁿ-chiok ê thong-sòe kì-lo̍k, kap chòe-kīn 10 pái súi ê tiāⁿ-chiok kì-lo̍k, tān-sī boán-tiâu chiàⁿ chin tō hui koh chiâⁿ pháiⁿ ê tùi-chhiú, lâi siau-chài.
Tī só͘-chāi ê tùi-chhiú tiong, ū kuí choân-pō͘ pí-lu̍t tùi Kansas State sī bô su-kò?
Hiam-ná ê tùi-chhiú boé-chiáp sī sím-mih, tō ū KSU chin tn̂g ê iâⁿ (W 8), tān-sī chòe-kīn 10 pái hō͘-chhan bô chin chán?
Tī-sio̍h-ê KST chhit tùi Vanderbilt ê sèng-lī chiàu-liáu, in ê sin Chi̍t-chóng kì-lo̍k sī KST, 7-5, chi̍t-ê sin chiân-tūi ki-lo̍k chhoán-chòe W 1?
answer: Sin ê Chi̍t-chóng kì-lo̍k ē chiâⁿ-chòe KST, 6-4, chi̍t-ê sin chiân-tūi ki-lo̍k chiâⁿ-chòe L 2 chiâⁿ-chòe W 1.

question: Tùi chit kho͘ chu-liāu lâi khòaⁿ, KSU tī 'Chòe-kīn 5 tiâu soán-táu' (chhiūⁿ 5-0 ia̍h 4-1) ū chi̍t ê tōa thong ê cheng-chek, kap in ê 'Tâi-tiâu chāi chāi' ū siáⁿ-mih koan-hē?
answer: Ū chi̍t ê kiông-kuh ê tòe-sûn koan-hē. Tī 12 ê tiâu kiâⁿ tang-tiong, ū 10 tiâu sī KSU tī chòe-kīn 5 tiâu soán-táu sī 4-1 ia̍h 5-0, koh ū hiān-chāi ê tòe-sûn sī iâⁿ. Put-kò, chit ê koan-hē m̄-sī oân-choân chòe-chèng. Chhiūⁿ kóng, chi̍t ê SMU, KSU tī chòe-kīn 5 tiâu soán-táu sī 4-1, tān-sī hiān-chāi sī tòe 1 tiâu, sī iâⁿ chiap, che sī kóng chòe-kīn ê soán-táu sī iâⁿ, tān-sī chiân-bīn ê cheng-chek sī tōa thong.

question: Giam-chāi lán ê tsu-liāu, ūi-tio̍h Kam-su-tat (Kansas State) kah i tan-tuāⁿ tsham-ka 10 pái í-hā ê tsiok-tē (opponent), "tsóng-thiu kóe" (Overall Record) kah "tsuì-āu 10 pái tsham-ka" (Last 10 Meetings) chit nn̄g ê muî-e̍h ūi-siáⁿ ū tsiânn-tsò tsuè-khuì (redundant) ê sìn-sit? Iâu-káu sī siáⁿ-mi̍h?
answer: "Tsóng-thiu kóe" (Overall Record) kah "tsuì-āu 10 pái tsham-ka" (Last 10 Meetings) chit nn̄g ê muî-e̍h ūi-tio̍h tsit-kuá tsiok-tē ū tsiânn-tsò tsuè-khuì (redundant) ê sìn-sit. Tang-sîh, tsham-ka ê tsóng-pái (total number of games played) sī 10 pái í-hā, "tsuì-āu 10 pái tsham-ka" ê kóe sī tiāu-tī tsóng-thiu kóe. Tsham-ka Kahn-li-hong (California) (tsham-ka 7 pái), nn̄g ê muî-e̍h lóng sī KSU, 6-1.

question: Tī chit ê tùi-chhiú hō͘ Kansas State iâⁿ nn̄g tiâu, che kā i hō͘ chioh-chè ê chu-liāu chin bē-tàng cháiⁿ-iūⁿ?
answer: Chit ê tùi-chhiú ê 'Chit-chūn chioh-chè' ē tiâⁿ-ka nn̄g tiâu iâⁿ ê sèng-lī, ē-tàng hō͘ hit ê tùi-chhiú chioh-chè ê sin kì-lù.
